Package es.fnl.fsm

Interface Summary
Transition<E> Transitions define how elements of a sequence should match to the pattern.
 

Class Summary
BFSQueue<E> A priority queue for breadth-first search that can backtrack the list of states that lead to some particular state.
ExactMatcher<T extends Transition<E>,E> A generic DFA for doing exact pattern matching.
Matcher<E> An engine that performs match operation on a sequence of generic elements E by interpreting a Pattern (analogous to Matcher).
Pattern<E> A generic, NFA-based pattern matching implementation using weighted backtracking and providing capture groups.
QueueItem<T> (Priority level, item) wrapper for the priority queue used in the breadth-first-search (BFS) implementation of the Matcher.
State<E> A State vertex with outgoing labeled (transition) and empty (epsilon) edges.
